[3] Chad: national emergency declared
Date: Wed 10 Jul 2019
Source: KFF (Henry J. Kaiser Family Foundation) via Al Jazeera [edited]
https://www.kff.org/news-summary/measles-cases-up-700-in-africa-who-says-chad-declares-national-emergency/


Al Jazeera: Cases of measles in Africa rise by 700%: UN body
"Parts of Africa are grappling with an outbreak of measles, and the preventable disease is making a comeback because many people here are not being vaccinated. The World Health Organization says cases on the continent have surged by 700% this year [2019] alone. Al Jazeera's Nicolas Haque reports from Chad, where a national emergency has been declared."

