[6] Ohio
Date: Fri 12 Jul 2019
Source: Cincinnati Enquirer [abridged, edited]
https://www.cincinnati.com/story/news/2019/07/12/measles-ohio-reports-first-case-year-stark-county/1712945001/


Ohio has its 1st case of measles, in a young Stark County adult, and the state's Health Department urged parents to vaccinate against the infectious disease.

State health director Dr. Amy Acton said Friday [12 Jul 2019] the person who got sick with measles had recently traveled to a state with confirmed measles cases. The case is the 1st confirmed instances of measles in 2 years. The last outbreak of the illness in Ohio was in 2014, with 382 confirmed cases.

The nation [USA] is experiencing a major spread of measles, with 28 states reporting cases.

[Byline: Anne Saker]

