[7] Michigan
Date: Thu 11 Jul 2019
Source: The Ticker [abridged, edited]
https://www.traverseticker.com/news/measles-case-confirmed-in-grand-traverse-county/


The Grand Traverse County Health Department confirmed Wednesday [10 Jul 2019] that it had received notification of a confirmed case of measles in a county resident.

According to the Health Department, the case involves an unvaccinated individual who recently traveled to Eastern Europe and returned to Traverse City. This is the 3rd instance of international travel-related measles cases in Michigan this year [2019].

[Byline: Beth Milligan]

